data.description: Looking for a quiet place to call home but still just minutes to dining and shopping?  110 Pebble Beach is just that place!  Built in 2019 this three bedroom, three full bath home is nestled in a natural buffer of trees offering privacy and seclusion yet just a short distance to HWY 17.  Options made by the Sellers have added desirability to the home to include tankless water heater, gas stove, gas logs and owned propane gas tank.  There is LVP throughout the main living level which is carried through to the master bedroom.  The split floor plan offers the master suite on one side of the home with two additional bedrooms and shared bath opposite.  In addition, there is a finished room over the garage with a full bath.  This could be another bedroom, craft room or gaming room.  In addition to the attached two car garage with epoxy finish floor is the 20 x 25 detached garage.  Whether you need a place to tinker, space for a home office (s) or additional garage/storage space, you are all set.  Relax in your screened porch, 16 x 10, grill on the patio or play yard games.  Inside and outside, there is great space for living and entertaining.  Yard maintenance is easy with an irrigation system and landscaping which is manicured but not 'fussy'.  Too many wonderful attributes to mention but waiting for you to view.  Make plans to see 110 Pebble Beach soon.   Non-HOA community.
